{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882105613,"sessionID":"ses_2852dfd68ffe1p0zOx4QAug39u","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad2696a001RisS1hqRcRidhh","messageID":"msg_d7ad2615200183IjwIUS1xaSys","sessionID":"ses_2852dfd68ffe1p0zOx4QAug39u","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_34c3b41a29574653966c5821","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Docker Multi-Stage Build Design — AR-032\n2: \n3: **Module:** `docker`  \n4: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Stage:** ST-1 completed\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Overview\n11: \n12: This document describes the technical implementation details for Docker multi-stage builds for three AgentCube components: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. The design follows container security best practices, optimizes for minimal image size, and ensures consistency across development, testing, and production environments.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Architecture\n17: \n18: ### Multi-Stage Build Pattern\n19: \n20: Each component uses a two-stage Dockerfile:\n21: \n22: ```\n23: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n24: │  Stage 1: Builder                   │\n25: │  - Base: golang:1.21-alpine         │\n26: │  - Downloads Go modules             │\n27: │  - Compiles static binary           │\n28: │  - CGO_ENABLED=0                    │\n29: └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n30:                   │\n31:                   ▼\n32: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n33: │  Stage 2: Runtime                   │\n34: │  - Base: alpine:3.19                │\n35: │  - Copies binary from builder       │\n36: │  - Non-root user (UID 1000)         │\n37: │  - Exposes port 8080                │\n38: └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n39: ```\n40: \n41: ### Component Mapping\n42: \n43: | Component | Dockerfile | Source Path | Binary Output | Runtime User |\n44: |-----------|------------|-------------|---------------|--------------|\n45: | Workload Manager | `docker/Dockerfile` | `./cmd/workload-manager` | `/workloadmanager` | `apiserver` (UID 1000) |\n46: | Router | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | `./cmd/router` | `/router` | `router` (UID 1000) |\n47: | Picod | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | `./cmd/picod` | `/picod` | `picod` (UID 1000) |\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Data Structures\n52: \n53: ### Docker Build Arguments\n54: \n55: ```dockerfile\n56: # Common to all Dockerfiles\n57: ARG GO_VERSION=1.21\n58: ARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\n59: ARG TARGETARCH=amd64\n60: ARG TARGETOS=linux\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### OCI Image Labels\n64: \n65: ```dockerfile\n66: # Applied to all images\n67: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"<component>\"\n68: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube <component> component\"\n69: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n70: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.version=\"<version>\"\n71: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.revision=\"<commit-sha>\"\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### Environment Variables (Runtime)\n75: \n76: | Variable | Component | Purpose | Required |\n77: |----------|-----------|---------|----------|\n78: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis server address | Yes |\n79: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis authentication | No (default: \"\") |\n80: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | Yes |\n81: | `PORT` | All | HTTP listen port | No (default: 8080) |\n82: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Kubernetes namespace | No (auto-injected via fieldRef) |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## API Contracts\n87: \n88: ### Docker Build Interface\n89: \n90: **Build Command:**\n91: ```bash\n92: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.<component> -t <image-name>:<tag> .\n93: ```\n94: \n95: **Build Context:** Repository root\n96: \n97: **Required Files in Context:**\n98: - `go.mod`, `go.sum`\n99: - `cmd/<component>/`\n100: - `pkg/`\n101: \n102: **Excluded Files (via `.dockerignore`):**\n103: - `.git/`\n104: - `bin/`, `pkg/` (build artifacts)\n105: - `*_test.go`\n106: - `*.md` (documentation)\n107: - `testing/`\n108: - `.pytest_cache/`, `__pycache__/`\n109: \n110: ### Container Runtime Interface\n111: \n112: **Exposed Port:** 8080 (all components)\n113: \n114: **Entrypoint:**\n115: - Workload Manager: `/workloadmanager`\n116: - Router: `/router`\n117: - Picod: `/picod`\n118: \n119: **Default CMD:**\n120: - Workload Manager: `[\"--port=8080\"]`\n121: - Router: `[\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`\n122: - Picod: `[\"--port=8080\"]`\n123: \n124: **Health Check:**\n125: ```dockerfile\n126: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n127:     CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## Error Handling\n133: \n134: ### Build-Time Errors\n135: \n136: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n137: |-------|-------|------------|\n138: | `go.mod not found` | Build context incorrect | Ensure build runs from repository root |\n139: | `build failed: package not found` | Source path mismatch | Verify `cmd/` and `pkg/` are in context |\n140: | `out of memory` | Insufficient builder resources | Increase Docker memory limit |\n141: | `COPY failed: file not found` | `.dockerignore` excludes required file | Review `.dockerignore` patterns |\n142: \n143: ### Runtime Errors\n144: \n145: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n146: |-------|-------|------------|\n147: | `permission denied` | Running as root when non-root expected | Ensure `USER` directive is applied |\n148: | `port already in use` | Port 8080 occupied | Override `PORT` environment variable |\n149: | `connection refused to Redis` | `REDIS_ADDR` not set or incorrect | Verify environment variable configuration |\n150: | `binary not found` | Build stage failed to produce binary | Check builder stage logs |\n151: \n152: ### Validation Failures\n153: \n154: The `validate.sh` script shall fail with non-zero exit code when:\n155: - Image size ≥ 50MB\n156: - Layer count > 5\n157: - Running as root user\n158: - Port 8080 not exposed\n159: - Health check not configured\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Testing Strategy\n164: \n165: ### Unit Tests (Dockerfile Syntax)\n166: \n167: **Test File:** `docker/Dockerfile.test` (optional linting stage)\n168: \n169: **Test Cases:**\n170: 1. All Dockerfiles pass `hadolint` validation\n171: 2. No hardcoded secrets in any layer\n172: 3. Base images use pinned versions (not `latest`)\n173: \n174: ### Integration Tests\n175: \n176: **Test Script:** `docker/test/build_test.sh`\n177: \n178: ```bash\n179: #!/bin/bash\n180: # Build all images and verify basic properties\n181: \n182: set -e\n183: \n184: IMAGES=(\n185:     \"workloadmanager:test\"\n186:     \"router:test\"\n187:     \"picod:test\"\n188: )\n189: \n190: for image in \"${IMAGES[@]}\"; do\n191:     echo \"Building $image...\"\n192:     docker build -f \"docker/Dockerfile.${image%%:*}\" -t \"$image\" .\n193:     \n194:     # Verify image exists\n195:     docker image inspect \"$image\" > /dev/null\n196:     \n197:     echo \"✓ $image built successfully\"\n198: done\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ### Container Runtime Tests\n202: \n203: **Test Script:** `docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n204: \n205: ```bash\n206: #!/bin/bash\n207: # Test container runtime behavior\n208: \n209: set -e\n210: \n211: test_container() {\n212:     local image=$1\n213:     local name=$2\n214:     \n215:     # Start container\n216:     docker run -d --name \"$name\" \"$image\"\n217:     \n218:     # Wait for health check\n219:     sleep 10\n220:     \n221:     # Check running status\n222:     if ! docker inspect --format='{{.State.Running}}' \"$name\" | grep -q true; then\n223:         echo \"✗ $name failed to start\"\n224:         docker logs \"$name\"\n225:         return 1\n226:     fi\n227:     \n228:     # Check non-root user\n229:     local user=$(docker exec \"$name\" id -u)\n230:     if [ \"$user\" != \"1000\" ]; then\n231:         echo \"✗ $name running as root (UID: $user)\"\n232:         return 1\n233:     fi\n234:     \n235:     # Cleanup\n236:     docker stop \"$name\" && docker rm \"$name\"\n237:     \n238:     echo \"✓ $name passed runtime tests\"\n239: }\n240: \n241: test_container \"workloadmanager:test\" \"wm-test\"\n242: test_container \"router:test\" \"router-test\"\n243: test_container \"picod:test\" \"picod-test\"\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ### Security Tests\n247: \n248: **Tool:** Trivy (optional)\n249: \n250: ```bash\n251: # Scan for vulnerabilities\n252: trivy image workloadmanager:latest --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1\n253: trivy image router:latest --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1\n254: trivy image picod:latest --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1\n255: ```\n256: \n257: ### Performance Tests\n258: \n259: **Metrics to Validate:**\n260: - Build time < 5 minutes per image (with cached dependencies)\n261: - Image size < 50MB per image\n262: - Layer count ≤ 5\n263: - Container start time < 2 seconds\n264: \n265: ---\n266: \n267: ## Implementation Details\n268: \n269: ### Workload Manager Dockerfile\n270: \n271: ```dockerfile\n272: # docker/Dockerfile\n273: # Multi-stage build for Workload Manager\n274: \n275: # Stage 1: Builder\n276: FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder\n277: \n278: WORKDIR /build\n279: \n280: # Cache Go modules\n281: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n282: RUN go mod download\n283: \n284: # Copy source code\n285: COPY cmd/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n286: COPY pkg ./pkg\n287: \n288: # Build static binary\n289: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n290:     -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n291:     -o /build/workloadmanager \\\n292:     ./cmd/workload-manager\n293: \n294: # Stage 2: Runtime\n295: FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n296: \n297: # Install CA certificates for HTTPS\n298: RUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n299: \n300: WORKDIR /app\n301: \n302: # Copy binary from builder\n303: COPY --from=builder /build/workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager\n304: \n305: # Create non-root user\n306: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\n307: \n308: # Set ownership\n309: RUN chown -R apiserver:apiserver /app\n310: \n311: # Switch to non-root user\n312: USER apiserver\n313: \n314: # Expose port\n315: EXPOSE 8080\n316: \n317: # Health check\n318: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n319:     CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n320: \n321: # Labels\n322: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"workloadmanager\"\n323: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Workload Manager component\"\n324: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n325: \n326: # Entrypoint\n327: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]\n328: CMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ### Router Dockerfile\n332: \n333: ```dockerfile\n334: # docker/Dockerfile.router\n335: # Multi-stage build for Router\n336: \n337: # Stage 1: Builder\n338: FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder\n339: \n340: WORKDIR /build\n341: \n342: # Cache Go modules\n343: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n344: RUN go mod download\n345: \n346: # Copy source code\n347: COPY cmd/router ./cmd/router\n348: COPY pkg ./pkg\n349: \n350: # Build static binary\n351: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n352:     -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n353:     -o /build/router \\\n354:     ./cmd/router\n355: \n356: # Stage 2: Runtime\n357: FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n358: \n359: RUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n360: \n361: WORKDIR /app\n362: \n363: COPY --from=builder /build/router /app/router\n364: \n365: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 router\n366: RUN chown -R router:router /app\n367: \n368: USER router\n369: \n370: EXPOSE 8080\n371: \n372: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n373:     CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n374: \n375: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"router\"\n376: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Router component\"\n377: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n378: \n379: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/router\"]\n380: CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ### Picod Dockerfile\n384: \n385: ```dockerfile\n386: # docker/Dockerfile.picod\n387: # Multi-stage build for Picod\n388: \n389: # Stage 1: Builder\n390: FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder\n391: \n392: WORKDIR /build\n393: \n394: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n395: RUN go mod download\n396: \n397: COPY cmd/picod ./cmd/picod\n398: COPY pkg ./pkg\n399: \n400: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n401:     -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n402:     -o /build/picod \\\n403:     ./cmd/picod\n404: \n405: # Stage 2: Runtime\n406: FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n407: \n408: RUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n409: \n410: WORKDIR /app\n411: \n412: COPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod\n413: \n414: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 picod\n415: RUN chown -R picod:picod /app\n416: \n417: USER picod\n418: \n419: EXPOSE 8080\n420: \n421: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n422:     CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n423: \n424: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"picod\"\n425: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Picod component\"\n426: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n427: \n428: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/picod\"]\n429: CMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n430: ```\n431: \n432: ### .dockerignore\n433: \n434: ```dockerignore\n435: # .dockerignore\n436: # Build context exclusions for efficient Docker builds\n437: \n438: # Version control\n439: .git\n440: .gitignore\n441: \n442: # Build artifacts\n443: bin/\n444: dist/\n445: *.out\n446: coverage.out\n447: \n448: # Dependencies (Go modules cached during build)\n449: vendor/\n450: \n451: # IDE and editor files\n452: .idea/\n453: .vscode/\n454: *.swp\n455: *.swo\n456: *~\n457: \n458: # Documentation\n459: *.md\n460: !README.md\n461: \n462: # Tests\n463: testing/\n464: *_test.go\n465: .pytest_cache/\n466: \n467: # Docker (avoid recursive copy)\n468: docker/\n469: Dockerfile*\n470: \n471: # Kubernetes manifests\n472: manifests/\n473: changes/\n474: \n475: # Python artifacts\n476: __pycache__/\n477: *.pyc\n478: *.pyo\n479: .eggs/\n480: *.egg-info/\n481: \n482: # OS files\n483: .DS_Store\n484: Thumbs.db\n485: \n486: # Logs\n487: *.log\n488: logs/\n489: \n490: # Temporary files\n491: tmp/\n492: temp/\n493: ```\n494: \n495: ---\n496: \n497: ## Makefile Integration\n498: \n499: ### Build Targets\n500: \n501: ```makefile\n502: # Docker configuration\n503: DOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh\n504: DOCKER_TAG ?= latest\n505: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n506: COMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n507: \n508: # Image names\n509: WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\n510: ROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\n511: PICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n512: \n513: # Build all images\n514: .PHONY: docker-build-all\n515: docker-build-all: docker-build-workloadmanager docker-build-router docker-build-picod\n516: \n517: # Build Workload Manager image\n518: .PHONY: docker-build-workloadmanager\n519: docker-build-workloadmanager:\n520: \t@echo \"Building Workload Manager image...\"\n521: \tdocker build \\\n522: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n523: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n524: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n525: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n526: \t\t.\n527: \t@echo \"✓ Workload Manager image built: $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n528: \n529: # Build Router image\n530: .PHONY: docker-build-router\n531: docker-build-router:\n532: \t@echo \"Building Router image...\"\n533: \tdocker build \\\n534: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n535: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n536: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n537: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n538: \t\t.\n539: \t@echo \"✓ Router image built: $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n540: \n541: # Build Picod image\n542: .PHONY: docker-build-picod\n543: docker-build-picod:\n544: \t@echo \"Building Picod image...\"\n545: \tdocker build \\\n546: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n547: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n548: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n549: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n550: \t\t.\n551: \t@echo \"✓ Picod image built: $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n552: \n553: # Push all images\n554: .PHONY: docker-push-all\n555: docker-push-all: docker-push-workloadmanager docker-push-router docker-push-picod\n556: \n557: # Push Workload Manager image\n558: .PHONY: docker-push-workloadmanager\n559: docker-push-workloadmanager:\n560: \t@echo \"Pushing Workload Manager image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n561: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n562: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n563: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n564: \n565: # Push Router image\n566: .PHONY: docker-push-router\n567: docker-push-router:\n568: \t@echo \"Pushing Router image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n569: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n570: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n571: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n572: \n573: # Push Picod image\n574: .PHONY: docker-push-picod\n575: docker-push-picod:\n576: \t@echo \"Pushing Picod image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n577: \tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n578: \tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n579: \tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n580: \n581: # Load images to Kind cluster\n582: .PHONY: kind-load-all\n583: kind-load-all: kind-load-workloadmanager kind-load-router kind-load-picod\n584: \n585: .PHONY: kind-load-workloadmanager\n586: kind-load-workloadmanager:\n587: \tkind load docker-image $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n588: \n589: .PHONY: kind-load-router\n590: kind-load-router:\n591: \tkind load docker-image $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n592: \n593: .PHONY: kind-load-picod\n594: kind-load-picod:\n595: \tkind load docker-image $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n596: \n597: # Multi-architecture build (requires Docker Buildx)\n598: .PHONY: docker-buildx-all\n599: docker-buildx-all: docker-buildx-workloadmanager docker-buildx-router docker-buildx-picod\n600: \n601: .PHONY: docker-buildx-workloadmanager\n602: docker-buildx-workloadmanager:\n603: \tdocker buildx build \\\n604: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n605: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n606: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n607: \t\t--push \\\n608: \t\t.\n609: \n610: .PHONY: docker-buildx-router\n611: docker-buildx-router:\n612: \tdocker buildx build \\\n613: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n614: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n615: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n616: \t\t--push \\\n617: \t\t.\n618: \n619: .PHONY: docker-buildx-picod\n620: docker-buildx-picod:\n621: \tdocker buildx build \\\n622: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n623: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n624: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n625: \t\t--push \\\n626: \t\t.\n627: \n628: # Clean up local images\n629: .PHONY: docker-clean\n630: docker-clean:\n631: \t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n632: \t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n633: \t-docker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n634: \t-docker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n635: \t-docker rmi $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n636: \t-docker rmi $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n637: ```\n638: \n639: ---\n640: \n641: ## File Structure\n642: \n643: ```\n644: deployment/docker/\n645: ├── Dockerfile                 # Workload Manager image\n646: ├── Dockerfile.router          # Router image\n647: ├── Dockerfile.picod           # Picod image\n648: ├── .dockerignore              # Build context exclusions\n649: ├── design.md                  # This file\n650: ├── delta-spec.md              # Delta specification\n651: └── test/\n652:     ├── build_test.sh          # Build integration tests\n653:     └── runtime_test.sh        # Container runtime tests\n654: ```\n655: \n656: ---\n657: \n658: ## Security Considerations\n659: \n660: ### Principle of Least Privilege\n661: \n662: 1. **Non-root execution:** All containers run as UID 1000 (non-root)\n663: 2. **Minimal capabilities:** No `--cap-add` required\n664: 3. **Read-only root filesystem:** Compatible with `securityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem: true`\n665: \n666: ### Supply Chain Security\n667: \n668: 1. **Pinned base images:** Use specific versions (`golang:1.21-alpine`, `alpine:3.19`)\n669: 2. **No secrets in images:** Credentials injected via Kubernetes Secrets/Environment\n670: 3. **Reproducible builds:** Static linking with `CGO_ENABLED=0`\n671: \n672: ### Attack Surface Reduction\n673: \n674: 1. **Minimal runtime:** Alpine 3.19 has ~5MB attack surface\n675: 2. **No shell access:** Optional hardening via `rm -rf /bin/sh` in runtime stage\n676: 3. **Static binaries:** No dynamic library vulnerabilities\n677: \n678: ---\n679: \n680: ## Performance Optimization\n681: \n682: ### Build Cache Optimization\n683: \n684: 1. **Layer ordering:** Copy `go.mod`/`go.sum` before source code\n685: 2. **Module caching:** `go mod download` runs before code changes\n686: 3. **Context exclusion:** `.dockerignore` reduces build context size\n687: \n688: ### Image Size Optimization\n689: \n690: 1. **Multi-stage build:** Build tools excluded from runtime\n691: 2. **Static compilation:** No glibc dependencies\n692: 3. **Minimal base:** Alpine 3.19 (~5MB) vs Debian (~100MB)\n693: \n694: Expected image sizes:\n695: - Workload Manager: ~25-35MB\n696: - Router: ~25-35MB\n697: - Picod: ~25-35MB\n698: \n699: ---\n700: \n701: ## Open Questions\n702: \n703: 1. **Multi-architecture support:** Should ARM64 builds be mandatory or optional?\n704: 2. **Distroless migration:** Should we migrate from Alpine to `gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11` for enhanced security?\n705: 3. **Version injection:** Should build version/commit be injected into binaries via `-ldflags`?\n706: 4. **Health check endpoint:** Should HEALTHCHECK use a dedicated endpoint or the main `/health`?\n707: \n708: ---\n709: \n710: ## References\n711: \n712: - `deployment/spec.md` — Deployment Specification\n713: - `deployment/design.md` — Deployment Design\n714: - `docker/delta-spec.md` — Delta Specification for AR-032\n715: - Docker Best Practices: https://docs.docker.com/develop/develop-images/dockerfile_best-practices/\n716: - Alpine Linux: https://alpinelinux.org/\n717: - Multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/\n718: \n719: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 719 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Docker Multi-Stage Build Design — AR-032\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-1 completed\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation details for Docker multi-stage builds for three AgentCube components: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. The design follows container security best practices, optimizes for minimal image size, and ensures consistency across development, testing, and production environments.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Multi-Stage Build Pattern\n\nEach component uses a two-stage Dockerfile:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/design.md","time":{"start":1775882105596,"end":1775882105611}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882105617,"sessionID":"ses_2852dfd68ffe1p0zOx4QAug39u","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad26e74001cuEmxc1K8h5NmE","messageID":"msg_d7ad2615200183IjwIUS1xaSys","sessionID":"ses_2852dfd68ffe1p0zOx4QAug39u","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_928c4f2270e041b79c41d500","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `docker`  \n6: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n7: **Size:** S  \n8: **Type:** Multi-stage Docker build for Workload Manager, Router, and picod container images\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-032.1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` for building the Workload Manager container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n21: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` is built with repository root as context\n22: - **WHEN** the build stage runs\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n26: - **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n27: - **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Workload Manager binary compilation\n31: - **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n32: - **WHEN** build runs\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n36: - **GIVEN** build stage completes\n37: - **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n41: - **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n42: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `apiserver` with UID 1000\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n46: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary is built\n47: - **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/workloadmanager`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Container port exposure\n51: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n52: - **WHEN** container runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Default command configuration\n56: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n57: - **WHEN** container starts without override\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL run `/workloadmanager` as entrypoint\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### REQ-032.2: Router Dockerfile\n63: \n64: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.router` for building the Router container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n67: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` is built with repository root as context\n68: - **WHEN** the build stage runs\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n72: - **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n73: - **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Router binary compilation\n77: - **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n78: - **WHEN** build runs\n79: - **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /router ./cmd/router`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n82: - **GIVEN** build stage completes\n83: - **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n87: - **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n88: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `router` with UID 1000\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n92: - **GIVEN** router binary is built\n93: - **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/router`\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Container port exposure\n97: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n98: - **WHEN** container runs\n99: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Default command configuration\n102: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n103: - **WHEN** container starts without override\n104: - **THEN** it SHALL run `/router` as entrypoint\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### REQ-032.3: Picod Dockerfile\n109: \n110: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.picod` for building the picod container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n113: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` is built with repository root as context\n114: - **WHEN** the build stage runs\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n118: - **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n119: - **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Picod binary compilation\n123: - **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n124: - **WHEN** build runs\n125: - **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod`\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n128: - **GIVEN** build stage completes\n129: - **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n130: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n133: - **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n134: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `picod` with UID 1000\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n138: - **GIVEN** picod binary is built\n139: - **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/picod`\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: Container port exposure\n143: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n144: - **WHEN** container runs\n145: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Default command configuration\n148: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n149: - **WHEN** container starts without override\n150: - **THEN** it SHALL run `/picod` as entrypoint\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ### REQ-032.4: Multi-stage Build Optimization\n155: \n156: **Requirement:** The system SHALL optimize Docker images for size and security through multi-stage build patterns.\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: Minimal runtime image\n159: - **GIVEN** multi-stage build completes\n160: - **WHEN** final image size is measured\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL be under 50MB for each component (Workload Manager, Router, picod)\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: No build tools in runtime\n164: - **GIVEN** runtime stage completes\n165: - **WHEN** image is inspected\n166: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT contain go compiler, git, or build dependencies\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Static binary linkage\n169: - **GIVEN** CGO_ENABLED=0 is set during build\n170: - **WHEN** binary runs in runtime stage\n171: - **THEN** it SHALL have no dynamic library dependencies\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Alpine base image\n174: - **GIVEN** runtime stage uses alpine:3.19\n175: - **WHEN** image is scanned for vulnerabilities\n176: - **THEN** it SHALL have minimal CVE surface compared to Debian-based images\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ### REQ-032.5: Security Best Practices\n181: \n182: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement container security best practices in all Dockerfiles.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Non-root user execution\n185: - **GIVEN** container starts\n186: - **WHEN** process runs\n187: - **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Read-only filesystem compatibility\n190: - **GIVEN** container runs with read-only root filesystem\n191: - **WHEN** application needs temporary storage\n192: - **THEN** it SHALL use `/tmp` volume mount if needed\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: No secrets in image\n195: - **GIVEN** Dockerfile is built\n196: - **WHEN** image layers are inspected\n197: - **THEN** they SHALL NOT contain hardcoded credentials, tokens, or API keys\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Minimal attack surface\n200: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n201: - **WHEN** shell access is attempted\n202: - **THEN** image MAY exclude `/bin/sh` to prevent shell injection (optional hardening)\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ### REQ-032.6: Build Context and .dockerignore\n207: \n208: **Requirement:** The system SHALL use efficient build context by excluding unnecessary files via `.dockerignore`.\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Exclude .git directory\n211: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n212: - **WHEN** build context is sent to Docker daemon\n213: - **THEN** `.git/` directory SHALL be excluded\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Exclude build artifacts\n216: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n217: - **WHEN** build context is sent\n218: - **THEN** `bin/`, `pkg/`, and `*_test.go` files SHALL be excluded from context\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Exclude development files\n221: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n222: - **WHEN** build context is sent\n223: - **THEN** `.md` files (except README if needed), `.gitignore`, and editor files SHALL be excluded\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Include only required files\n226: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` is configured\n227: - **WHEN** build runs\n228: - **THEN** context SHALL include only: `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `cmd/`, `pkg/`, and any required configs\n229: \n230: ---\n231: \n232: ### REQ-032.7: Makefile Integration\n233: \n234: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building all three Docker images.\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: Build Workload Manager image\n237: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-workloadmanager` target\n238: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-workloadmanager` runs\n239: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `workloadmanager:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile`\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Build Router image\n242: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-router` target\n243: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` runs\n244: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `router:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Build picod image\n247: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-picod` target\n248: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` runs\n249: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `picod:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Build all images\n252: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-all` target\n253: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` runs\n254: - **THEN** it SHALL build all three images sequentially\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Push Workload Manager image\n257: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-push-workloadmanager` target with `REGISTRY` variable\n258: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-workloadmanager REGISTRY=registry.example.com` runs\n259: - **THEN** it SHALL tag and push image to `registry.example.com/workloadmanager:latest`\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Push all images\n262: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-push-all` target with `REGISTRY` variable\n263: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-all REGISTRY=registry.example.com` runs\n264: - **THEN** it SHALL tag and push all three images to specified registry\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ## Data Types\n269: \n270: ```dockerfile\n271: # Docker build arguments (common to all Dockerfiles)\n272: ARG GO_VERSION=1.21\n273: ARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\n274: ARG TARGETARCH=amd64\n275: \n276: # Labels for image metadata\n277: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"<component>\"\n278: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube <component> component\"\n279: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n280: ```\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## File Structure\n285: \n286: ```\n287: docker/\n288: ├── Dockerfile           # Workload Manager image\n289: ├── Dockerfile.router    # Router image\n290: ├── Dockerfile.picod     # Picod image\n291: └── .dockerignore        # Build context exclusions (shared or per-Dockerfile)\n292: ```\n293: \n294: ---\n295: \n296: ## Make Targets\n297: \n298: | Target | Description |\n299: |--------|-------------|\n300: | `docker-build-workloadmanager` | Build Workload Manager image |\n301: | `docker-build-router` | Build Router image |\n302: | `docker-build-picod` | Build picod image |\n303: | `docker-build-all` | Build all three images |\n304: | `docker-push-workloadmanager` | Push Workload Manager image to registry |\n305: | `docker-push-router` | Push Router image to registry |\n306: | `docker-push-picod` | Push picod image to registry |\n307: | `docker-push-all` | Push all images to registry |\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ## Environment Variables\n312: \n313: | Variable | Component | Purpose | Default |\n314: |----------|-----------|---------|---------|\n315: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis server address | - |\n316: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis authentication | \"\" |\n317: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | - |\n318: | `PORT` | All | HTTP listen port | 8080 |\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ## Acceptance Checklist\n323: \n324: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile` — Workload Manager multi-stage build\n325: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.router` — Router multi-stage build\n326: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.picod` — Picod multi-stage build\n327: - [ ] `docker/.dockerignore` — Build context optimization\n328: - [ ] Make targets for building all three images\n329: - [ ] Make targets for pushing images to registry\n330: - [ ] Non-root user in all runtime images\n331: - [ ] Alpine 3.19 base for minimal image size\n332: - [ ] CGO disabled for static binaries\n333: - [ ] Port 8080 exposed in all images\n334: - [ ] Image size under 50MB each\n335: - [ ] OCI labels for image metadata\n336: - [ ] Go module cache optimization (go.mod copied first)\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ## Open Questions\n341: \n342: 1. Should Dockerfiles support multi-architecture builds (ARM64, AMD64) via `--platform` flag?\n343: 2. Should health check instructions (`HEALTHCHECK`) be added to Dockerfiles?\n344: 3. Should distroless images be used instead of Alpine for enhanced security?\n345: 4. Should build version/commit be injected into images via `ARG` at build time?\n346: \n347: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 347 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** Multi-stage Docker build for Workload Manager, Router, and picod container images\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-032.1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` for building the Workload Manager container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n\n#### Scenario: Build stage configuration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882105599,"end":1775882105614}}}}
